,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"3eccbc7aae7c850972a6c6f3fee3b8829bdeb27e","tid":2075323,"uid":334191,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"quote":{"pid":"907287d8dcca22005369b46c53f0a36d0df03a65","tid":2075323,"uid":359022,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-22T20:38:16.000Z","msg":"欣賞你打簡體字的堅持和勇氣<br />\n但是 如果想擁有更廣闊的討論 <br />\n融入當地文化會比較容易一些<br />\n應該會慢慢有人跟你交流"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-06-24T10:08:57.000Z","msg":"谢谢你的建议。不过简体字和繁体字都是你们华人的文字，对我来说差不多。在中国的时候不曾融入华人，现在生活在英语国家就更不打算融入华人了。"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-24T10:40:11.000Z","msg":"我的意思是說如果你想在這個討論區有人和你展開討論，用繁體融入討論區文化會有幫助<br />\n就這樣<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"13c8c0f3843e5f131efd8bba23faccecd0bb9136","tid":2075323,"uid":334191,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-26T00:36:32.000Z","msg":"&quot;黑命贵&quot; (Black lives are expensive), the Chinese mistranslation for Black Lives Matter, is based on a popular mindset of rating lives with money. It prices white lives highest, Chinese slightly cheaper &amp; blacks worthless. It sees racial equity as the overpricing of black lives. &quot;黑人的命也是命&rdquo;被偷换成&ldquo;黑命贵&rdquo;，是因为在中文语境里，生命常常是分贵贱的，可以用金钱来衡量。在不少华人看来，白人的命最昂贵，其次是他们自己的命，而黑人的命最不值钱。黑人走上街头要求获得作为人的平等权利，这让他们难以接受，觉得黑人在为自己的生命在漫天要价。"},{"pid":"01c87130e8cd948a62910f4021f5270f3ab721c2","tid":2075323,"uid":334191,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-06-26T00:37:33.000Z","msg":"中国著名维权律师<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/scDsPAm.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FscDsPAm.jpg&h=1f3f08cd&s={SIZE}\" />"}]}